This is an `O(1)` operation that just increases the reference count
and sets a few indices.

# Examples

```
use bytes::BytesMut;

let mut a = BytesMut::from(&b"hello world"[..]);
let mut b = a.split_off(5);

a[0] = b'j';
b[0] = b'!';

assert_eq!(&a[..], b"jello");
assert_eq!(&b[..], b"!world");
```

# Panics

Panics if `at > capacity`.

